data.name: checkBoxSunOverlay.ToolTip
data.value:
Only works if Enable Weather Selector is disabled, Day/Night Color Shift is Enabled & Location entered is valid.
Wallpaper overlay color based on sunrise-sunset time for the day - instead of 6am-6pm in regular mode. Night birghtness is fixed in this mode, unlike the linear fashion in regular color shift mode. Note: sunrise-sunset time is calculated based on system time zone; so if you are entering a location othan than your own then disable this.

data.name: DXVABox.ToolTip
data.value: (Experimental) Hardware Accelerated Video Playback. Lower CPU & RAM usage; expecially for higher resolution videos. If enabled, 90% of processing is done via GPU - High gpu usage. Application will be locked at 60fp regardless of FPS setting. Video is affected by color settings in gpu control panel.

data.name: qualityDrop.ToolTip
data.value:
Blur is resource heavy (gpu). Blur processing quality level, higher value corresponds to better blur. Low/High/Very High - 2/16/64 samples Mipmaps are used to reduce processing, texture will appear pixelated at low settings.
Recommended: High on systems with dedicated gpu. Low lower end intel graphics systems.

data.name: apiKey_richTextBos.Text
data.value:
Change existing openweathermap.org weather key if weather stops working. Follow the following steps (free) :-
1. Signing up at: https://openweathermap.org/ 2. Goto API Keys. 3. Create a key if none present. 3. Copy paste the newly created key over "default" text. 4. New Key can take some time to activate, if you get "4xx Error" retry after sometime.
To revert back to the original bundled key, change the field to "default" without quotes
